            "Name": "Morning Star",
            "Description": "An orb about 4 inches in diameter, made of metal or some other hard material. It has several small holes that allow the vapors from it's contents to escape.",
            "History": "",
            "Application": "Thrown",
            "Effects": "As an action, you can throw this grenade at a point up to 30 feet away. At the start of your next turn, it emits an opaque cloud of poisonous gas filling a 20-foot radius sphere. Each creature that is completely within the cloud at the start of its turn must make a Constitution saving throw (DC 12) or become poisoned for 1 minute. A creature can make the saving throw again at the start of each of its turns, ending the poisoned condition on a success. [p]Additionally, the gas ignites violently on contact with an open flame, and each creature in the area must make a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw. A target takes 4d6 fire damage on a failed save, or half as much on a successful one. The gas dissipates naturally over a period of up to 1 minute, depending on the wind conditions.",
            "EffectCategory": "Offensive",
            "Duration": "Special",
